<title>NETHERLANDS: Reed-Elsevier sells Folio Corp.</title>
<headline>Reed-Elsevier sells Folio Corp.</headline>
<dateline>AMSTERDAM 1997-02-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Anglo-Dutch publishing group Reed-Elsevier said on Friday it would sell its U.S. unit Folio Corp to Open Market Inc.</p>
<p>&quot;The purchase consideration will be $45 million, to be paid partly in cash and partly in stock of Open Market Inc., which is quoted on NASDAQ,&quot; Reed-Elsevier said in a statement.  </p>
<p>Folio, which develops information publishing software, was acquired by Reed-Elsevier in December 1994 as part of the Anglo-Dutch publisher's purchase of LEXIS-NEXIS.</p>
<p>Reed-Elsevier said it would continue and extend the technical partnership with Open Market Folio divisions on the supply of information retrieval software.</p>
